Synchronous communication, eventual consistency, orchestration

Orchestrator manages requests, response and error handling but is not responsible for managing transactions
Orchestrator may manage compensating calls but without the requirement of occurring within an active transaction

Compared to other patterns this one generally exhibits a favorable set of tradeoffs
Consider if eventual consistency is an option

Qualities
    Communication               Synchronous
    Consistency                 Eventual
    Coordination                Orchestrated
    Coupling                    High
    Complexity                  Very Low
    Responsiveness/availability Medium
    Scale/elasticity            High